main event: On 14 November 1957, radar surveillance at Rothwesten, Germany, detected three high-speed unidentified objects.
interesting points: The targets were detected across various times over a span of hours,They exhibited high speeds during the observations,One radar blip split into two different targets,The investigation concluded that observed blips were likely false returns rather than actual aircraft,Unusual electronic interference was reported during the sightings.
witness description: military personnel including Sergeants and Lieutenants
